		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.89]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Pilapeu&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>start out with a 1hb in your off hand, this not drasticly reducing your damage output, but steadily raising your 1hb. doing it this way will take probably 4-5 levels to get it maxed out. But once you get your 1hb up to 30 or 40 you can feel free to put the 1hb in your good hand or dual weild 1hb. then your skill will be high enough you won't feel bad for lack of damage AND your skill will go up faster. Also once you max out your 1hb you'll probably want to think about training your 2hb. I had a big problem with this too, because i felt i was letting my group down, but if you're not the main tank then don't worry. a group with more than one tank usually won't mind. I recently had a lot of fun grouping with 5 other monks. we all decided to work on our 2hb, so I went and bought a staff and we proceded to thrash a few hundred blues because that was pretty much all we could handle. it was very funny. Also at 15 it's a lot easier to practice your 2hb without feeling bad because you'll get double attack so your skill will go up twice as fast. <br><br>/em does the spock thing and says live long and prosper young monkey</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Pilapeu Wewingtonheet<br>SilentFist Clan<br>Seventh Hammer Server</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
