		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Heyas, my monk is 11th so she's just a skip ahead of you. However, for the skills I think she has you beat by a bit. I not here to laud my monk but to tell you how I went about keeping most of her skills up.<br><br>Of course, you know that skill points are easier to increase when they get out of the early stages (i.e. Feeble-Awful). I usually try to switch weapons right after I get to a certain level. Moderation is the key here. Certainly don't get overly buffed in H2H and be weak in 1HB or 2HB. I am trying to raise all the skills at these lowly levels b/c it does SUCK when you can only club a MoB at 10th level for 1 or 2 damage. However, you do have to practice and hopefully your group will understand that. <br><br>The (obvious) thing I do to increase the weapon skills of my monk was to solo blues and blacks while using the lower (or lowest) skill (i.e. 1HB for my case - I know how powerful those 2HB weapons are later!). You'll survive the fight 99% of the time b/c you have your kick/claw as well. At the same time, you are increasing your skill point. My monk is in Butchers Block and there are plenty of things to solo (one or two at a time) which spawn often. Perhaps you can do likewise in your locale. <br><br>Don't forget your safefall skill either :)<br><br>P.S. Pilapeu - wish I could have joined your group. A hoard of XP-hungry monks is worse than the gestapo!</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table